1. Make sure the path to your private key file (~/UserKey.pem) is correct and that you have read permissions on the file.
2. Ensure that the AWS Access Key ID and Secret Access Key associated with the EC2 instance are properly set up in your environment. This can be done by adding them to the appropriate configuration files (e.g., ~/.aws/credentials) or by setting environment variables.
3. If you're using a firewall on your local machine, make sure that it is configured to allow incoming SSH traffic from the EC2 instance's IP address (ec2-34-221-131-108.us-west-2.compute.amazonaws.com).
4. Verify that the port number you specified in your command (25900) is available on your local machine and that it doesn't conflict with any other services or programs running on that port.
